==English==

===Etymology===
From Russian ''[[погром]]''

===Noun===
'''pogrom'''  (''plural:'' '''[[pogroms]]''')
# The [[persecution]] of a particular group, usually on the basis of their [[religion]] or [[ethnic]] origin.  Pogroms took place in czarist Russia, during a period known as the Russification, which was proposed by Alexander III in order to protect the autocracy and build the feeling of nationalism among the citizens.


